📌 Results
Successfully segmented customers into five distinct customer groups using K-Means clustering.
Identified high-value customer segments with above-average credit limits for premium product targeting.
Detected potential underserved customer groups with higher income but comparatively lower credit limits.
Developed segment-level business KPIs to support data-driven marketing, customer retention, and credit management strategies.
Visualized customer clusters using both summary charts and a 3D scatter plot for easier interpretation.

📚 Future Improvements
Determine the optimal number of clusters using the Elbow Method and Silhouette Score instead of selecting a fixed value.
Include additional customer features such as age, spending behavior, transaction frequency, utilization ratio, and account tenure.
Compare K-Means with other clustering algorithms such as Hierarchical Clustering, DBSCAN, and Gaussian Mixture Models.
Build an interactive customer segmentation dashboard using Power BI or Tableau.
Deploy the segmentation model as a web application using Streamlit for real-time customer profiling.

